worldcoin is doubling on self custody:

wallet & world id private keys already live locally on people's personal device, and now so will orb data

this gives everyone even more control over how to use it, and of course even to delete it

full details below

https://worldcoin.org/blog/announcements/worldcoin-implements-personal-custody
builders build
wym signing permanent identity on chain?

yup, there is no onchain identity

world id is a separate self custodial private key

orb simply “stamps it as verified” without linking biometrics

every time you use world id you do it through zkps, essentially creating a disposable id for every app

https://x.com/worldcoin/status/1762234361649221803?s=20

was deleted by default but you had the option to back up in servers

self custody gives you the privacy of deletion with convenience of backup

+ you get to press the delete button personally, which people seem to prefer

more info:

https://worldcoin.org/blog/announcements/worldcoin-implements-personal-custody
